Package: rikus-updateall
Version: 1.2
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Gilbert Rikus <gilbert@rikus.info>
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Depends: python3, python3-gi, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, dpkg, apt
Recommends: polkitd | policykit-1, pkexec | policykit-1
Suggests: flatpak, npm
Homepage: https://github.com/Zahnschmerz/rikus-updateall
Description: Find and update programs that do not come from apt
 apt only knows packages from configured sources. Everything installed by
 hand - a .deb downloaded from a website, an AppImage, a program dropped into
 /usr/local/bin, an npm package - grows old silently. Nothing ever says so.
 .
 Rikus Updateall lists exactly those programs, checks each one against its
 vendor, and updates them on request. It covers manually installed .deb
 packages, AppImages, Flatpaks, plain program files and npm packages, and it
 calls a program's own updater where one exists.
 .
 The origin is read from the package itself wherever possible - Homepage and
 Vcs fields for .deb, the built-in update information for AppImages - so it
 also works for programs it has never heard of. Where nothing is found, the
 source can be entered once and is remembered.
 .
 Nothing is changed without a plain-language preview first. Downloads are
 verified before anything is replaced, the previous version is kept, and the
 result is measured afterwards instead of assumed. Administrator rights are
 requested only for the replacement itself, never for looking.
 .
 User interface in German or English, chosen automatically.
